            <div class="article-body">
                                                                                                                    <div class="asset_media asset-media">
                                                <amp-iframe width="640" height="360" layout="responsive" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin" allowfullscreen frameborder="0" src="//web.archive.org/web/20200529061749if_/https://embed.sendtonews.com/amp/?fk=0QFvHiBV&amp;cid=9587&amp;offsetx=0&amp;offsety=0&amp;floatwidth=400&amp;floatposition=bottom-right&amp;url=https://www.stamfordadvocate.com/business/article/Former-Stamford-UBS-site-sells-for-33-million-12442382.php">
                            <amp-img layout="fill" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20200529061749im_/https://d29xw9s9x32j3w.cloudfront.net/players/library/placeholder.png" placeholder></amp-img>
                        </amp-iframe>
                    </div>
                                                                    <div class="amp-ad">
                    <amp-ad height="250" width="300" type="doubleclick" data-slot="/36117602/hnp-stamfordadvocate.mobile/Business" json="{&quot;targeting&quot;:{&quot;page_type&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;position&quot;:&quot;ATF&quot;,&quot;DIV_ID&quot;:&quot;A300&quot;,&quot;page_type2&quot;:&quot;Amp&quot;}}" rtc-config="{&quot;vendors&quot;:{&quot;aps&quot;:{&quot;PUB_ID&quot;:&quot;3070&quot;,&quot;PARAMS&quot;:{&quot;amp&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}},&quot;prebidappnexus&quot;: {&quot;PLACEMENT_ID&quot;: 18920456, &quot;ACCOUNT_ID&quot;: &quot;403ca951-6d92-4f2b-816a-0cf8a69217d8&quot;}},&quot;timeoutMillis&quot;: 750}">
                    </amp-ad>
                </div>
                                                                                                                                                                            <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p>STAMFORD &mdash; The site of the city&rsquo;s largest vacant office complex has been sold to an affiliate of the California investment firm that bought its mortgage earlier this year, a move city officials hope will help to revive the struggling property.</p>
                                                                                                                                                    <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p>Stamford Washington Investors LLC bought the lot last week for $33 million, according to city property records. It contains an approximately 700,000-square-foot structure that formerly housed the local offices of investment banking giant UBS and what was once the world&rsquo;s biggest trading floor. The building has stood empty since UBS last year moved across the street to 600 Washington Blvd., which also houses offices for Royal Bank of Scotland.</p>
                                        <div class="amp-ad">
                    <amp-ad height="250" width="300" type="doubleclick" data-slot="/36117602/hnp-stamfordadvocate.mobile/Business" json="{&quot;targeting&quot;:{&quot;page_type&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;position&quot;:&quot;BTF&quot;,&quot;DIV_ID&quot;:&quot;B300&quot;,&quot;page_type2&quot;:&quot;Amp&quot;}}" rtc-config="{&quot;vendors&quot;:{&quot;aps&quot;:{&quot;PUB_ID&quot;:&quot;3070&quot;,&quot;PARAMS&quot;:{&quot;amp&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}},&quot;prebidappnexus&quot;: {&quot;PLACEMENT_ID&quot;: 18920456, &quot;ACCOUNT_ID&quot;: &quot;403ca951-6d92-4f2b-816a-0cf8a69217d8&quot;}},&quot;timeoutMillis&quot;: 750}">
                    </amp-ad>
                </div>
                                                                                                                                    <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s always ideal to gain control of the &lsquo;dirt&rsquo; of the property,&rdquo; said Christian Bangert, executive vice president of Stamford commercial real estate firm Rhys. &ldquo;Knowing the additional capital that will be needed to re-tenant the building and bring it up to modern office infrastructure levels, you really want to have as much control as possible and for as long as possible.&rdquo;</p>
                                                                                                                                                    <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p>The buyer&rsquo;s listed business address is also that of Beverly Hills, Calif.-based AVG Partners, which acquired the property&rsquo;s loan in April for about $54 million. The listed address of the seller, Gateway Land Corp., is 600 Washington Blvd.</p>
                                                                                                                                                    <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p>Alongside the sale of 677 Washington, two AVG affiliates bought two adjoining lots for a total of approximately $7 million, while UBS acquired another neighboring parcel for free from the AVG group, according to city records. Those parcels encompass vacant land around the office building.</p>
                                                                                                                                                    <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p>Messages left Tuesday for AVG and UBS were not immediately returned.</p>
                                                            <div id="NTVAmp1Free" class="amp-ad">
                <amp-ad type="nativo" height="280" width="375" layout="responsive" data-request-url="https://amp.stamfordadvocate.com/amp/nativo">
                </amp-ad>
            </div>
                                                                                                            <meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><p></p>
                                                                                                                                                                                                                            <amp-base-carousel id="gallery" class="amp-carousel" width="auto" height="425" layout="fixed-height">
                            
                    <div class="asset_photo" data-slide-id="1">
                        <div class="img-wrap">
                            <amp-img class="amp-img" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20200529061749im_/https://s.hdnux.com/photos/70/13/41/14727236/5/375x250.jpg" width="375" height="249" layout="fixed">
                            </amp-img>
                        </div>
                                                                                                                        <div>
                            <div class="mediasale"> <span class="icon"> </span> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20200529061749/http://stamfordadvocate.mycapture.com/mycapture/remoteimage.asp?backtext=Back%20to%20Stamford%20Advocate&amp;image=https://s.hdnux.com/photos/70/13/41/14727236/5/628x471.jpg&amp;pricingsheetid=2241">Buy this photo</a></div>
                            <span class="credit">
                                                Photo: Michael Cummo / Hearst Connecticut Media
                                            </span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="caption">
